<h2>Event Management</h2>
<p>
    The tools are accessible when the user is identified and has the necessary rights. A toolbar appears on each page. It is also possible to manage the pages from <a href="{{ path('events_dashboard') }}">{{ 'label.dashboard'|trans }} (Events)</a>.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>Create a page</strong>: use the button <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-plus class btn btn-default btn-xs"></span>
    <br />
    <strong>Modify a page</strong>: use the button <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil class btn btn-default btn-xs"></span>
    <br />
    <strong>Delete a page</strong>: use the button <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-trash class btn btn-default btn-xs"></span>
    <br />
    <strong>View the current version of a page</strong>: use the button <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-eye-open class btn btn-default btn-xs"></span>
</p>

<h2>Data requirements</h2>
<p>
    For each page it is necessary to provide
    <br />
    <strong>Title</strong>: Used to be displayed on the event and sent to the browser
    <br />
    <strong>Semantic url</strong>: link used to call the event, for example: http://example.com/pages/<strong>semantic-url</strong>, only unaccented lowercase letters and '-'. It is set automatically according to the title, but it can be changed.
    <br />
    <strong>Picture</strong> : picture for the event
    <br />
    <strong>Start date and time</strong> : in connection with the event
    <br />
    <strong>End date and time</strong> : in connection with the event
    <br />
    <strong>Place</strong>: in connection with the event
    <br />
    <strong>Description</strong>: description of the event
</p>

